snippet.title: Coke Studio Bharat | Leta Jaijo Re | Shashwat Sachdev x Sunidhi Chauhan x Chotu Khan
snippet.description:
The legacy of Rajasthani culture echoes its history from its palatial havelis, speaks of furtive & shy romances through its stone walls and sings folk songs of tradition & meticulous courtship, cherished and passed down through generations. 
‘Leta Jaijo Re’ is sung like a love song but experienced as a celebration. The song celebrates the beginning of a young couple’s love story, through the willingness to give away a token of your love. 
Acclaimed music super producer Shashwat Sachdev strings together this piece of cultural story-telling through his global yet rooted pallette weaving beautifully Sunidhi Chauhan’s contemporary prowess.

snippet.title: Coke Studio Bharat | Sonchadi | Instrument Spotlight
snippet.description:
The synergy of a group of talented musicians is what really brought the tale of Rajula and Malushahi to life. An assortment of authentic Kumaoni instruments simply elevated the listening experience of #Sonchadi – the sarangi is a short-necked three-stringed instrument, usually made from a single block of wood. Shaped like a damru, the handcrafted hudka is an authentic Uttarakhandi instrument. Accompanying them was the soulful notes of the flute  and the classic sound of the dholak, while they even used a kansa thali as an instrument! The keys, guitars and drums gave the track its new-age feel. 


#Sonchadi #CokeStudioBharat #CokeStudio #uttarakhand

snippet.title: Coke Studio Bharat | Sonchadi | Neha Kakkar x digV x Kamala Devi

From within the forests of Uttarakhand come the sounds of secrets that only nature holds, but if you listen carefully you’ll also hear a love story, whispered through the rustling of the leaves and repeated through the gurgling of the streams.

A love story that is centuries old, but known throughout the hills even today. The story of Rajula and Malushahi. First penned only in the 1930's this beautiful folklore echoes in the forest even today.

Let the music of the hills and this epic love story of #Sonchadi guide you to listen to the song of your heart.

snippet.title: Coke Studio Bharat | Chirmathi | MC SQUARE x Mohito x Hashbass Feat. Karsh Kale
snippet.description:
Remember the dreams you had when you were a child? Forget what the world has to say and live your dreams! "Chirmathi" is the story of every young girl who dared to dream and soar high to conquer the skies. It captures her transition from a young girl who, after shedding her wings of innocence, is getting ready to take flight towards her dreams. As she looks back on all the comforts of childhood with nostalgia, she also readies herself to ignore all the voices that doubt her ability to fly. Through this collaboration, MC Square and Mohito pay homage to all the 'Chirmathi's' who dared to fly high in pursuit of their dreams. Stitching together this evocative narrative are, versatile Hashbass on bass & synth and renowned percussionist Karsh Kale, who, through their electro-percussion fusion, give the song a dynamic energy.
